Description: Kicknote.com is a web-based portal that provides its users with up-to-date information about music, artists, movies, and food.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Kicknote.com provides users with a fun and easy way to stay up to date on their favorite musical artists, while delivering new and interesting content that might ordinarily slip through the cracks. Now a music-lover can ensure he/she always gets the latest information by simply taking a few moments to browse through his/her Kicknote account; no more searching through multiple sites or repeated Googling. It might be helpful to think of the Kicknote stream as a sort of modified RSS reader in which rather than subscribing to specific sources (i.e. sites), users are able to subscribe to specific topics (i.e. artists) and receive information on those topics from a wide variety of sources, each contributing its own special kind of unique content. To get started quickly and easily, Kicknote suggests a list of artists based on a user's iTunes data file. Once a user finishes customizing the proposed list, all of the artists are added to his/her Stream and he/she immediately starts receiving categorized, filtered, real-time updates on those artists, gathered from across 50+ sites, including, currently: Twitter updates, videos, and photos; and coming soon: blog posts, tickets, music, merchandise, news stories, interviews, and more. Kicknote is also currently working on expanding into other areas of interest, such as sports, to create one place for users to get a comprehensive view of everything about their favorite players and teams. News stories, highlights, photos, scores, interviews, Twitter updates, game tickets, merchandise, and more will all be constantly flowing into the Kicknote sports stream, making sure you stay up to date on all of your teams all year long. After sports, areas such as celebrities, movies, television, and even health/medicine will be added as well. In short, Kicknote is here to help manage the ever-increasing amount of content on the Internet.
Industry Groups: Apps, Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment, Music and Audio, Software, Sports, Video
Founders: Brian Erickson, Mike Cunningham, Rob Hicks, Tom Hallett

SecSign Technologies delivers user authentication, messaging, file sharing, and file storage with next-generation security for company networks, websites, platforms, and devices. Using advanced cryptography, SecSign eliminates passwords, simplifies authentication, and provides messaging and file data solutions that make it virtually impossible for hackers to compromise user accounts or access sensitive information. Founded in 1998, we have dedicated ourselves to developing security software to provide our customers and their users with the highest level of security. Our parent company, SecCommerce, was one of the first companies in the world to guarantee security for data archiving and communication for large insurance companies, banks, and national institutions by using electronic signature components. Government and social insurance agencies, which must follow strict guidelines and meet high standards of security and privacy, rely on our solutions every day to provide maximum protection for sensitive data. For 15 years, our software solutions have been used millions of times to secure long-term archiving, communication, and access to online portals. Along the way, we have continued to earn the trust of public and private institutions that value our experience and expertise. SecCommerce’s software solutions provide accessible software keys and smart card technology for portal, workflow and archiving needs. Our products offer and connect existing “Public Key Infrastructures” (PKI) and ensure timely implementation for customers in private industry and the public sector. But the benefits resulting from our know-how are not limited to national institutions or major corporations. SecSign Technologies Inc. represents our effort to extend our expertise and make it readily available to organizations and institutions of all types and sizes, and even for individual users.
